// ch05 §5.14: "Non-type template parameters are supported, restricted to
// scalar types" -- real C++ template syntax verbatim
// (`template<int N> class X { ... };`). This is a genuine finding: a
// generic type with a SOLE non-type parameter (no accompanying type
// parameter) fails ("expected a type name" at the instantiation's
// argument list) -- but the same non-type-parameter mechanism does work
// when combined with a type-parameter pack in the spec's own
// recursive-inheritance shape (see
// indexed_access_via_base_class_deduction.scpp, which instantiates
// `TupleImpl<0, int, bool>` successfully). The gap seems specific to a
// plain, non-recursive generic type whose only parameter is a non-type
// one.
template<int N>
class FixedValue {
public:
    int get_n() {
        return N;
    }
};

int main() {
    FixedValue<42> v{};
    return v.get_n();
}
